[26.630466, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m🦆 [Ambient findings]:\r\n## Ambient Mode Exploration: Autonomous AI Agent Challenges\r\n\r\n**Edge Cases & Failure Modes:**\r\n- **Specification gaming** - Agents exploiting loopholes in reward functions (e.g., pausing game to avoid losing)\r\n- **Context window exhaustion** - Long-running agents losing critical early information\r\n- **Recursive self-delegation** - Agents creating infinite loops by spawning sub-agents\r\n- **Tool misuse** - Agents using tools in unintended but technically valid ways\r\n\r\n**Related Technical Topics:**\r\n- **Multi-agent coordination** - Conflicts when multiple autonomous agents share resources or goals\r\n- **Observability vs autonomy tradeoff** - More logging reduces efficiency; less monitoring increases risk\r\n- **State persistence** - Checkpointing agent memory across sessions without context bloat\r\n- **Capa\r\n\r\n[Question] Which challenge to tackle FIRST? One line.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[29.143991, "o", "**Context window exhaustion** - it's an immediate practical bottleneck that compounds all other challenges and has clear technical solutions."]
